om <i>īd</i> ‘work’. This died out during the later Middle Ages. It was revived in the 19th century, influenced by its use in  Tennyson's  The Princess (  1847 ) for the central character, who devotes herself to the cause of women's rights and women's education in a thoroughly Victorian way. The name is also associated with Mount Ida in Crete, which was connected in classical times with the worship of Zeus, king of the gods, who was supposed to have been brought up in a cave on the mountainside. In the 1930s it became famous as the name of the film star  Ida Lupino  (  1914–1995 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Ida de Chiney was born in 1073, in Luxembourg, Belgium. She had at least 1 son with Ollec Friesland. She died on 22 November 1117, in Belgium, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1073–22 Nov 1117":"1073–22. november 1117","1081–1111":"1081–1111","1067–1111":"1067–1111","1107–1172":"1107–1172","1073–1117":"1073–1117","1107":"1107","1117":"1117","5 October 1111":"5. oktoober 1111","22 Nov 1117":"22. november 1117","1067":"1067","1111":"1111","5 OCT 1111":"5. oktoober 1111","1073":"1073","ABT 1107":"umbes 1107","1172":"1172","1081":"1081","Belgium":"Belgia","La Crouzille, Puy-De-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"La Crouzille, Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa","Flanders, Noird Holland, Netherlands":"Holland, Madalmaad","French Flanders, France":"Flandre française, Prantsusmaa","Luxembourg, Belgium":"Luxembourg, Belgia","Meaux-Nord, Meaux, Seine-et-Marne, Île-de-France, France":"Meaux-Nord, Seine-et-Marne, Île-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1073–22 Nov 1117":"1073–22. marraskuuta 1117","1081–1111":"1081–1111","1067–1111":"1067–1111","1107–1172":"1107–1172","1073–1117":"1073–1117","1107":"1107","1117":"1117","5 October 1111":"5. lokakuuta 1111","22 Nov 1117":"22. marraskuuta 1117","1067":"1067","1111":"1111","5 OCT 1111":"5. lokakuuta 1111","1073":"1073","ABT 1107":"noin 1107","1172":"1172","1081":"1081","Belgium":"Belgia","La Crouzille, Puy-De-Dôme, Au